SCENE STRUCTURE GUIDANCE
=========================
A practical logistics conversation between partners:
  1. Agenda — one partner raises the scheduling or planning topic.
  2. Information exchange — dates, constraints, options discussed back and forth.
  3. Problem-solving — a small complication arises and is resolved cooperatively.
  4. Side conversation — one or both partners goes off-topic briefly (work, children, plans).
  5. Resolution — the coordination topic is settled; conversation winds down.
